i did this and didnt see any snapshots. Time Machine local (APFS) snapshots are not visible in Finder or most standard macOS UI, but they can be viewed and managed directly in the macOS Disk Utility app in recent versions of macOS (Monterey or later).

See Snapshots in the UI
Open the Disk Utility app (found in Applications > Utilities).

From the menu bar, select View > Show APFS Snapshots.

Select your boot/data volume in the sidebar.

A table listing all APFS snapshots for that volume appears at the bottom of the window. You can view the name, creation date, cumulative size, and other metada incorporate this into web search and /research

Bug: Incorrect Analysis Period Causes Metric Inflation
The analysis period from 2024-12-25 to 2025-08-23 is listed as 70 days, but it actually spans approximately 241 days. This incorrect day count causes all daily average metrics throughout the document (e.g., commits/day, PRs/day) to be significantly inflated.
